               <p>SECOND COUNT, for uttering and publishing the same as true.</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182702150094"></xptr>GEORGE WILLIAM EVANS. I am a <rs id="t18270215-250-viclabel1341" type="occupation">potatoe-dealer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270215-250-victim1324 t18270215-250-viclabel1341"></join>, and live in Spitalfields. On the 17th of October I was in a public-house in Barbican; I had a horse there - the prisoner asked me to sell it; another person wanted me to sell it, and take a bill of him, which I refused; I at last agreed to sell it to the prisoner for 4l. 10s. - he threw down this cheque for eight guineas; I said I had no change - he said he would go home with me for it; I said I had no money, and would go home with him for it; some persons in the room, who appeared then to be strangers to him, proposed that I should take the cheque, and present it next morning, and he call on me for the change; he objected to that - I wished to have nothing to do with it; I waited, as he said if he could sell a poney, he could give me the money; I at last said, if he wished the horse, he was to call on me in the morning, but I did not care about selling it; the others interfered, and wished him to give me the cheque; I got up to go away - he then said, "Give me your direction, and what money you have got - I'll call to-morrow for the rest;" he then gave me the cheque; I gave him the horse and 19s. - he did not call in the morning; Newland, who was with me, said he had known him a long time, and it was all right; the prisoner gave me his direction, No. 3, Fan-street; next morning I went with the cheque, and found the bankers had failed ten months ago - he never called for the change.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270215-250-person1325">
                  ROBERT 
                  BOOTH
               <interp inst="t18270215-250-person1325" type="surname" value="BOOTH"></interp>
